<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/902863-urgent---please-help-a-cataclyst-is-the">URGENT - Please help!!
A Cataclyst is the Dark version of a Natural. But from what I can tell, there are no Light Evos and Sirens, meaning these two types of Casters are inherently Dark? Seeing as we know Ryan is a Thaumaturge before her Claiming, we can infer that Ridley was born a Siren. Does that mean she&#39;s been bound to go Dark her whole life? How does the Claiming system work for Evos and Sirens?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_902863'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F7930335-beautiful-redemption">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/902863-urgent---please-help-a-cataclyst-is-the">5 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/902863-urgent---please-help-a-cataclyst-is-the">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/57308505-kristyn-garza-the-bibliophile-empress"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1521738524i/57308505._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/57308505-kristyn-garza-the-bibliophile-empress">Kristyn  Garza (The Bibliophile Empress)</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    Before the Order was broken and then changed you'd be correct in saying that there are no Light Evos and no Light Sirens, however, after the Order was<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    Before the Order was broken and then changed you'd be correct in saying that there are no Light Evos and no Light Sirens, however, after the Order was broken by Lena and then fixed by Ethan, it can be inferred that (since the new Order is now not just Dark and Light but both) there is a possibility for Evos and Sirens to choose the Light if they wanted. It's true that there is no Light counterpart to Evos and Sirens but with the new Order, there is now an opportunity for Evos and Sirens to choose to be either Dark or Light. Now Ryan is a special case, it's been stated many times before. Ryan began exhibiting signs of being a Thaumaturge when she was very young (dare I say, toddler young) and this is an abnormality and exception. This fact also shows that she will more than likely be one of the world's most powerful Thaumaturges. Ridley only began exhibiting signs of becoming a Siren the months leading up to her claiming as she felt herself going Dark. So no, she was not born to be a Siren, that's just how her cards played out. The claiming system works just as it does for any other caster as it does for Sirens and Evos. Except for the Duchannes women of course, they don't really get a choice between Light or Dark it kind of just claims them. But remember, all other caster families (men and women) are able to claim themselves for either Dark or Light so the claiming system works for Evos and Sirens as it does for anyone else. A caster's powers may begin to lean one way or the other but it is ultimately their choice to become what they want, so someone can choose to become an Evo or a Siren but that (in the old Order) would be inherently choosing to be Dark, but with the new Order it could possibly just be a simple choice between Light or Dark Evo or Siren. I hope that answers all your questions.<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
</div>
